item.description:
After exiting the plane yesterday in Norfolk, Virginia, after 57 years, U.S. Navy Capt. Thomas E Scheurich has finally returned home. Yesterday , American Airlines brought him home to Norfolk, VA, where he was honored with the dignity and respect he deserves. Welcome home, Capt. item.title: It's good advice
item.description: I'm neither vegan nor vegetarian, and while I respect the beliefs that lead to that, it's not for me. But I also think our meat industry is generally pretty shitty, so I also like to minimize my meat consumption. I think this is not only a good way of thinking about meat consumption, but also anything related to problematic consumption. I'd like to boycott all the companies that do evil things, but… that's most of them, or maybe even all of them to some degree or another. But I can at least minimize my consumption from companies I know are worse vs. just completely abandoning trying altogether. It's a principle that seems obvious, but I thought it was worth sharing as a reminder to myself and anyone else who would benefit. :)

item.description: I posted this on the internet and the internet got mad that I painted "wolverine wrong" and when I explained I was x23 they told me I should have found an audio that said "x23" instead of wolverine and then I gave up. Please be sentient in the comments, I have been on a blocking spree with some gross people I use body paint and do these in a mirror No, it is not AI I just looked at an anatomical drawing of a skeleton and copied it I use professional body paint covers (pasties) this means I am not wearing a top but I am also not naked. I paint myself, I make the props myself, I film myself, and I also edit. This is my full time thing now (yayy) I paint these by looking in a mirror, with brushes, and paint It takes between 6-12 hours each Body painting myself is my hobby/passion I do own clothes It doesn’t tickle “Why don’t you just wear clothes” once again, body painting myself is my hobby/passion. I know, even I think this is a ridiculous set of questions I have to constantly answer I did not go to art school, I am self taught. Talent gets you so far, but this is a learned skill. The paint isn’t edible (gross) I've been painting myself for 16 years. The 07 does not mean I was born in 2007, UK 7 is my shoe size No, I don't need help painting my back, I don't want to paint my back, I don't need to paint my back. (also gross) No, I don't need help washing it off. (also you are gross) If you want to see more I am MCroft07 on IG, twitter, Tiktok, YouTube I paint them live on twitch I like doing the lip syncs, they're fun for me while I paint them. I couldn’t care less if you think they’re cringe. I am cringe but I am free My tattoos on my ribs are from Tomb Raider - I am a big TR fan I do not have an OF but if you want to send me money THAT badly you can just tip my twitch account. Haha. The shower afterwards takes about 15 minutes, I use a regular sponge and shower gel. The reason why it can look different at the end is because I am wearing a wig, I promise you it is not a different person because the hair changed. While on this topic, if my eyes change colour it’s because I am wearing contact lenses. (Those with an IQ above 10… I know. Even I’m shocked the wig thing is a frequent comment). I use body paint. It doesn’t tickle, I am very ticklish and this is fine. I don’t have an allergic reaction to the paint, but if you do it, you should always do a patch test first I do not know where you can buy body paint in every country. I know in the UK it is available at FacePaintingshop.com. I use a plethora of different brands, it’s best to search for them yourself online. I don’t work in Hollywood, I don’t want to. I just want to improve my body painting for myself. I am English, not American. I do not go outside like this to scare people. 1, that would be very cold. 2, in this current age, everyone would take photos without me knowing and it would likely dox me :)))))) I’m not a sweaty person, but if I was this would be a lot more difficult. Thank you to those of you who came from Imgur to my Twitch channel! “What’s the point in painting yourself when you can wear clothes?” all my clothes are in the laundry, had to resort to this, tough life It would not be quicker to jump into a pool of paint - think of the drying time?! If you're still here I'm procrastinating cleaning my wig wardrobe by posting this I don’t care that I wash it off at the end, I get to reuse this canvas, we love a reduce, reuse, recycle queen. I am not the lady who did the Maneskin video, it’s a cool video and she slayed, but it isn’t me. I can promise you there is not *a man* painting these and I am pretending to paint myself. I am genuinely painting myself. I know a lot of you don’t like reading this faq because it is horrid to see that I have to answer all of these. Unfortunately I have noticed that when I don’t put in all the icky things then I get more gross comments and I just have to spend more time blocking people so it’s better to call it out. I just copy and paste it each time anyway.

item.title: A Rare View Under the Sea Ice in Antarctica
item.description:
A view from above the ice overlooking Black Island, Discovery, and The Royal Society Mountains
The Observation Tube is a pipe with an undersea pod on the end to allow us to view the sea crits under the ice. Cue Super Mario Bros pipeDescent.wav
They have to lock it when SAR isn't active so we don't get stuck in there lol. SAR is always active, but they don't want to have to fish us out of here at three in the morning. We have to go in groups of no less than two and check out with the Central Communications Office before venturing out onto the sea ice. One person has to remain on the surface with a radio. Only one person can physically fit in the tube at a time. People have likely tried to fit more tho <_< Imagine getting having to call SAR to rescue you from a hookup cuz your horny asses got stuck in the toob lol
It's a really tight fit. we can't wear our Big Red parkas in there because they're too bulky
The tube is not advised for people who are claustrophobic. I am, but went anyway, because I may never have this opportunity again. The first couple of rungs, I was definitely feeling the anx, but I continued scared anyway. The tube hasn't been installed in the last two years because of sea ice instability and for other safety reasons. I jumped on this opportunity as soon as I could! My friends tried to fuck with me by sliding the lid back on and pretending to lock it, but I was far too focused on the vibe down here
My ambition was well rewarded with some stunning views under the ice
The minnows really like to be close to the bottom of the ice
The sea floor is about sixty feet down. Looking toward Ross Island, I could see the floor with a sea star chillin (3:00, middle)
I didn't see any penguins or seals while down there, but I could hear the chirps of a seal off in the distance. Under water they sound like some sci-fi lazer gunz. I wish I could have captured some audio, but it's faint, and my friends on the surface couldn't shut up for very long. We were all understandably excited. I hope to go back after everyone who wants to gets a chance to toob. I'd like to sit down here and meditate.
Above water the seals have a distinct honk. It's cute as hell. If you unmute, you might be able to hear it over my friends chatting, and my audible gasp reacting to it
I see da Minnow Fin tax with a few jellys As always, Thanks for reading!
item.dc:creator: VosperOfAntarctica
